AA.name: Party to be billed (AAR Accounting rule 11)
AA.desc: Party to be billed in accordance with AAR Accounting rule 11.

AB.name: Buyer's agent/representative
AB.desc:
Third party who arranged the purchase of merchandise on behalf of the
                                    actual buyer.

AE.name: Declarant's agent/representative
AE.desc:
Any natural or legal person who makes a declaration to an official
                                    body on behalf of another natural or legal person, where legally permitted (CCC).

AF.name: Transit principal
AF.desc:
Natural or legal person responsible for the satisfactory performance
                                    of a Customs transit operation. Source: CCC.

AG.name: Agent/representative
AG.desc: (3196) Party authorized to act on behalf of another party.

AH.name: Transit principal's agent/representative
AH.desc: Agent acting on behalf of the transit principal (CCC).

AI.name: Successful job applicant
AI.desc: Person who has been chosen for a job.

AJ.name: Party issuing mutually agreed codes
AJ.desc:
The party which has issued all mutually agreed codes used in the

AK.name: Acknowledgement recipient
AK.desc: Party to whom acknowledgement should be sent.

AL.name: Principal
AL.desc:
(3340) Party accepting liability for goods held or moving (e.g.
                                    transit) under a Customs authorization and - when applicable - a guarantee.

AM.name: Authorized official
AM.desc:
Employee of a company or firm authorized to act on behalf of that
                                    company or firm e.g. to make a Customs declaration.

AN.name: Approved importer
AN.desc:
Person or company which is authorised by the relevant Customs
                                    authority to import goods without payment all taxes or specific taxes at the point
                                    of entry into the country.

AP.name: Accepting party
AP.desc: (3352) Party accepting goods, products, services etc.

AQ.name: Approved consignor
AQ.desc:
Person or company approved by the relevant authority in the country to
                                    pack and export specific goods under Customs supervision.

AR.name: Authorized exporter
AR.desc:
Exporter authorized/approved by Customs for special Customs procedures
                                    e.g. simplified procedure.

AS.name: Account servicing financial institution
AS.desc: Identifies the financial institution servicing the account(s).

AT.name: Authorized importer
AT.desc:
Importer authorized/approved by Customs for special Customs procedures
                                    e.g. simplified procedure.

AU.name: Authorized trader (transit)
AU.desc:
Trader authorized/approved by Customs for special transit procedures
                                    e.g. simplified procedure.

AV.name: Authorizing official
AV.desc:
Party that has delegated the authority to take a certain action on
                                    behalf of a company or agency.

AW.name: Applicant's bank
AW.desc:
Financial institution which is requested to issue the documentary
                                    credit.

AX.name: Authenticating party
AX.desc: Party which certifies that a document is authentic.

AZ.name: Issuing bank
AZ.desc:
Financial institution which issues the documentary credit, if the
                                    applicant's bank is not acting as the issuing bank.

B1.name: Contact bank 1
B1.desc:
Identifies an additional bank which must be informed of certain
                                    aspects of the message.

B2.name: Contact bank 2
B2.desc:
Identifies an additional bank which must be informed of certain
                                    aspects of the message.

BA.name: Booking agent
BA.desc:
Party acting as a booking office for transport and forwarding
                                    services.

BB.name: Buyer's bank
BB.desc: [3420] Bank employed by the buyer to make payment.

BC.name: Negotiating bank
BC.desc:
Financial institution to whom a negotiable documentary credit is
                                    directed.

BD.name: Documentary credit reimbursing bank
BD.desc: A financial institution which reimburses documentary credit.

BE.name: Beneficiary
BE.desc:
The ultimate recipient of the funds. Normally the account owner who is
                                    reimbursed by the payor.

BF.name: Beneficiary's bank
BF.desc: Identifies the account servicer for the beneficiary or the payee.

BG.name: Employer
BG.desc: A party that keeps a person in service for payment.

BI.name: Buyer's financial institution
BI.desc: Financial institution designated by buyer to make payment.

BJ.name: Release to party
BJ.desc: Party to which the goods or container(s) is (are) to be released.

BM.name: Insured
BM.desc: Party which is the object of an insurance contract.

BN.name: Insurance beneficiary
BN.desc: Party which benefits from insurance coverage.

BO.name: Broker or sales office
BO.desc: Party acting in the name of the seller as broker or as sales office.

BP.name: Building site purchaser
BP.desc:
Party at the building site responsible for the purchasing of goods and
                                    services for that particular site.

BQ.name: Cheque drawn bank
BQ.desc:
Identifies the bank on which the cheque should be drawn, as instructed
                                    by the ordering customer.

BS.name: Bill and ship to
BS.desc: Party receiving goods and relevant invoice.

BT.name: Party to be billed for other than freight (bill to)
BT.desc: Party receiving invoice excluding freight costs.

BU.name: Service bureau
BU.desc:
Party carrying out service bureau processing work, (e.g. a payroll
                                    bureau).

BV.name: Member
BV.desc: Member of a group (e.g. of a group of persons or a service scheme).

BW.name: Borrower
BW.desc:
A person who acquires something temporarily with the promise or
                                    intention of returning.

BX.name: Building site engineer
BX.desc:
Party at the building site responsible for engineering matters for
                                    that particular site.

BY.name: Buyer
BY.desc: Party to whom merchandise and/or service is sold.

BZ.name: Building site forwarder
BZ.desc:
Party at the building site responsible for forwarding the received
                                    goods on that particular site.

C1.name: In care of party no. 1
C1.desc: A person taking responsibility on behalf of party no. 1.

C2.name: In care of party no. 2
C2.desc: A person taking responsibility on behalf of party no. 2.

CA.name: Carrier
CA.desc:

                                    points.

CB.name: Customs broker

Agent or representative or a professional Customs clearing agent who

CC.name: Claimant

CE.name: Ceding company
CE.desc: Company which cedes something to someone.

CF.name: Container operator/lessee

Party to whom the possession of specified property (e.g. container)

CG.desc: Party authorized to act for or on behalf of carrier.

CH.name: Connecting carrier

Owner or operator of a transportation conveyance to which goods in a

CI.name: Commission processor

CJ.name: Previous member
CJ.desc: Previous member of a group of persons or a service scheme.

CK.name: Empty equipment despatch party
CK.desc:
Party from whose premises empty equipment will be or has been
                                    despatched.

CL.name: Container location party
CL.desc: Party from whose premises container will be or has been despatched.

CM.name: Customs
CM.desc:
Identification of customs authority relevant to the transaction or
                                    shipment.

CN.name: Consignee
CN.desc: (3132) Party to which goods are consigned.

Identification of a financial institution servicing the top account of

CNY.name: Cash pool level account servicing financial institution

Identification of a financial institution servicing the level account

CNZ.name: Cash pool sub-account servicing financial institution

Identification of a financial institution servicing the sub-account of
                                    a cash pool.

CO.name: Corporate office
CO.desc: Identification of the Head Office within a company.

COA.name: Entity in which a financial interest is held
COA.desc: Business in which a financial interest is held.

COD.name: Quotation requesting party
COD.desc: Party sending a request for a quotation.

COE.name: Party maintaining the codes used in the message

COF.name: Party maintaining the identifiers used in the message

COG.name: Dispatcher

COH.name: Submitter of sample
COH.desc: An entity responsible for the submission of a sample.

COJ.name: Primary health care provider
COJ.desc: Health care provider that has primary responsibility for patient.

COL.name: Admitting health care provider
COL.desc: Health care provider that admitted the patient.

COM.name: Referring health care provider

Health care provider that referred patient to current provider of
                                    services.

CON.name: Supervising health care provider
CON.desc: Health care provider that supervised the rendering of a service.

COO.name: Party providing financing
COO.desc: Identifies the party providing the financing.

COP.name: Convoying party
COP.desc: Party designated to escort the transported goods.

COS.name: Co-participant
COS.desc: Identifies another party who participates in an activity.

COT.name: Involved party
COT.desc: Party which is involved in an activity.

COV.name: Registered principal

COW.name: Freight payer on behalf of the consignor
COW.desc: Freight payer is a third party acting on behalf of the consignor.

COX.name: Freight payer on behalf of the consignee
COX.desc: Freight payer is a third party acting on behalf of the consignee.

COY.name: Party responsible for disinfection
COY.desc: Party responsible for performing disinfection operations.

COZ.name: Party responsible for refueling
COZ.desc: Party responsible for performing refueling operations.

CP.name: Party to receive certificate of compliance

Party acting for or on behalf of seller in matters concerning
                                    compliance.

CPA.name: Advising bank

Identifies the financial institution used by the issuing bank to
                                    advise the documentary credit.

CPB.name: Reimbursing bank
CPB.desc:
Identifies the financial institution through which the reimbursement
                                    is to be effected.

CPC.name: Advise through bank
CPC.desc:
Identifies the financial institution through which the advising bank

CPD.name: Charges payer at destination

Party, other than the ordering party, which has to pay the charges

CPF.name: Means of transport charterer

CPG.name: Excise party
CPG.desc: Party to whom excise must be paid.

CPH.name: Copy report to
CPH.desc: Party receiving a copy of a report.

CPI.name: Related healthcare party
CPI.desc: A healthcare party related to the subject.

CPM.name: Patient discharged to
CPM.desc: The party who receives the discharged patient.

CQ.name: Cheque order
CQ.desc:
Party to which the cheque will be ordered, when different from the
                                    beneficiary.

CR.name: Empty equipment return party
CR.desc: Party to whose premises empty equipment will be or has been returned.

CS.name: Consolidator
CS.desc: Party consolidating various consignments, payments etc.

CT.name: Consignee to be specified
CT.desc: The party to be identified at a later time as the consignee.

CU.name: Container return company
CU.desc: The company to which containers have to be returned.

CV.name: Consignee of vessel
CV.desc: Party to which the vessel shall be delivered.

CX.name: Consignee's agent
CX.desc: Party authorized to act on behalf of the consignee.

CY.name: Commissionable agent

DA.name: Available with bank (documentary credits)

DB.name: Distributor branch

Party that splits up a large consignment composed of separate
                                    consignments of goods. The smaller consignments of goods were grouped together into
                                    that large consignment for carriage as a larger unit in order to obtain a reduced
                                    rate.

DCP.name: Despatch charge payer
DCP.desc:
Party, other than the ordering party, which has to pay the charges
                                    concerning the despatch operations.

DCQ.name: Prescription database owner
DCQ.desc: Organisation or person owning a prescription database.

DCR.name: Original prescriber
DCR.desc: The doctor who issued the original prescription.

DCS.name: Temporary employee
DCS.desc: A person employed on a temporary basis.

DCU.name: Quotation delivered to
DCU.desc: Party to whom the quotation is to be or has been delivered.

DCX.name: Party to receive refund
DCX.desc: Party to whom a refund is given.

DCY.name: Authorised issuer of prescription
DCY.desc: Party authorised to issue a prescription.

DCZ.name: Authorised dispenser of medicine
DCZ.desc: Organisation or person authorised to dispense medicine.

DD.name: Documentary credit account party's bank
DD.desc: Bank of the documentary credit account party.

DDA.name: Report responsible party
DDA.desc: The party or person taking responsibility for a report.

DDB.name: Initial sender
DDB.desc: The party who does the initial sending.

DDC.name: The party authorising the original prescription
DDC.desc: The party authorising the issuer of the original prescription.

DDD.name: Applicant
DDD.desc: A party who applies for something.

DDE.name: Meter reader
DDE.desc: A party physically reading the meter.

DDF.name: Primary electronic business contact
DDF.desc:
Code specifying a party who serves as a business entity's primary
                                    contact for matters related to electronic business.

DDG.name: Alternate electronic business contact
DDG.desc:
Code specifying a party who serves as a business entity's alternate
                                    contact for matters related to electronic business.

DDH.name: Primary government business contact
DDH.desc:
Code specifying a party who serves as a business entity's primary
                                    contact for matters related to doing business with the government.

DDI.name: Alternate government business contact
DDI.desc:
Code specifying a party who serves as a business entity's alternate
                                    contact for matters related to doing business with the government.

DDJ.name: Past performance contact
DDJ.desc:
Code specifying a party who serves as a business entity's contact for
                                    matters related to the past performance of that entity.

DDK.name: Balance responsible party
DDK.desc: A party responsible for balancing supply and consumption.

DDL.name: Group of passengers
DDL.desc:
A group of persons conveyed by a means of transport, other than the

DDN.name: First financial institution in the transaction chain
DDN.desc:
Identifies the financial institution that is the point of entry into

DDO.name: Location manager

DDP.name: Group leader
DDP.desc: Party responsible for leading the group.

DDR.name: Consignor's freight forwarder

DDS.name: Consignee's freight forwarder
DDS.desc: Identification of freight forwarder giving services to the consignee.

The movement of a crew member from one country to another via the

DDU.name: In transit passenger

The movement of a passenger from one country to another via the
                                    territory of an intermediate country for which no entry is intended.

A party who can be brought to rights, legally and financially, for any

DDW.name: Energy production imbalance responsible party

A party who can be brought to rights, legally and financially, for any
                                    imbalance between energy sold and produced for all associated metering points.

DDX.name: Imbalance settlement responsible party
DDX.desc:
A party that is responsible for settlement of the difference between
                                    planned and realised quantities.

DDY.name: Transmission capacity allocator

DDZ.name: Metering point administrator
DDZ.desc:
A party responsible for registering the technical specifications of
                                    metering points and the parties linked to them.

DE.name: Depositor
DE.desc: Party depositing goods, financial payments or documents.

DEA.name: Metered data aggregator
DEA.desc: A party responsible for aggregation of metered data.

DEB.name: Meter operator
DEB.desc:
A party responsible for the operation of a meter, including installing

DEC.name: Party connected to grid

A party that contracts for the right to consume or produce electricity

DF.name: Documentary credit applicant

Party at whose request the applicant's bank/issuing bank is to issue a
                                    documentary credit.

DG.name: Documentary credit beneficiary

Party in whose favour the documentary credit is to be issued and the
                                    party that must comply with the credit's terms and conditions.

DH.name: Documentary credit account party

Party which is responsible for the payment settlement of the

                                    documentary credit applicant.

DJ.name: Party according to documentary credit transaction

DK.name: Documentary credit beneficiary's bank

Financial institution with which the beneficiary of the documentary
                                    credit maintains an account.

Company offering a financial service whereby a firm sells or transfers
                                    title to its accounts receivable to the factoring company.

DM.name: Party to whom documents are to be presented

DO.name: Document recipient
DO.desc: (1370) Party which should receive a specified document.

DP.name: Delivery party

(3144) Party to which goods should be delivered, if not identical with

DQ.name: Owner's agent

DR.name: Driver

DS.name: Distributor
DS.desc: Party distributing goods, financial payments or documents.

DT.name: Declarant

(3140) Party who makes a declaration to an official body or - where

                                    body is made.

DU.name: Owner's representative
DU.desc:
Person commissioned by the owner to represent him in certain
                                    circumstances.

DV.name: Project management office

Party commissioned by the owner to follow through the execution of all
                                    works.

DW.name: Drawee
DW.desc: Party on whom drafts must be drawn.

DX.name: Engineer (construction)

Party representing the contractor to advise and supervise engineering
                                    aspects of the works.

DY.name: Engineer, resident (construction)

Party commissioned by the owner to advise and supervise engineering
                                    aspects of the works.

DZ.name: Architect

A designer who prepares plans for buildings, ships, etc. and

EB.name: Building inspectorate

Party controlling the conformity of works to legal and regulation

EE.name: Location of goods for customs examination before clearance

EF.name: Project coordination office

EI.name: Controller, quality
EI.desc:
Party controlling the quality of goods and workmanship for the

EJ.name: Surveyor, quantity

Party responsible for the quantification and valuation of the works on

EK.name: Surveyor (professional), quantity
EK.desc:
Party responsible to the owner for the quantification and valuation of
                                    the works.

EL.name: Project
EL.desc: Party responsible for a project, e.g. a construction project.

EM.name: Party to receive electronic memo of invoice

EN.name: Tenderer

EP.name: Equipment drop-off party
EP.desc: The party which drops off equipment.

EQ.name: Empty container responsible party
EQ.desc: Party responsible for the empty container.

ER.name: Empty container return agent

Party, designated by owner of containers, responsible for their

ES.name: Contractor, lead
ES.desc: Leader representing a grouping of co-contractors.

ET.name: Co-contractor
ET.desc: Member of a grouping of co-contractors.

EU.name: Contractor, general

Single contractor for the whole construction project, working by his

EV.name: Subcontractor
EV.desc: Firm carrying out a part of the works for a contractor.

(3030) Party who makes - or on whose behalf a Customs clearing agent

EY.name: Subcontractor, nominated

EZ.name: Operator, essential services
EZ.desc: Operator of essential services e.g. water, sewerage system, power.

FB.name: Nominated freight company

FC.name: Contractor, main

Firm or grouping of co-contractors which has been awarded the
                                    contract.

FE.name: Credit rating agency

FF.name: Factor, correspondent

Factoring company engaged by another factoring company to assist the

FG.name: Buyer as officially registered

FH.name: Seller as officially registered

FI.name: Copy message to

FK.name: Previous Trade Union

FL.name: Passenger

FM.name: Crew member

FN.name: Tariff issuer
FN.desc: The issuer of a tariff, e.g. a freight tariff.

FP.name: Freight/charges payer

FQ.name: Container survey agent

FR.name: Message from

FS.name: Party authorized to make definite a contract action

FT.name: Party responsible for financial settlement

(3450) Party responsible for either the transfer or repatriation of

FU.name: Hazardous material office

The office responsible for providing information regarding hazardous

FV.name: Party providing government furnished property

FZ.name: Grouping centre

GB.name: Chamber of commerce

Name of the Chamber of Commerce of the town where the company is

GD.name: Producer

GE.name: Registration tribunal

GG.name: Warehouse

GH.name: Applicant for job
GH.desc: A person who applied for a job.

GL.name: Socially insured person

GM.name: Inventory controller

GN.name: Processor
GN.desc: Party or person who has or will apply a process.

GO.name: Goods owner

GP.name: Packer

GQ.name: Slaughterer

GR.name: Goods releaser
GR.desc: (3026) Party entitled to authorize release of goods from custodian.

GS.name: Consignor's representative
GS.desc: Party authorised to represent the consignor.

GT.name: Rail carrier

GU.name: Originator of article number

GV.name: Procurement responsibility for order

GW.name: Party fulfilling all operations

Code indicating the fact that the party identified carries out all

GZ.name: Substitute supplier

Party which may be in a position to supply products or services should

HA.name: Party which delivers consignments to the terminal

HC.name: Transit freight forwarder

Freight forwarder to whom transit consignments are addressed, and from

HD.name: Inspection and acceptance party

HE.name: Transportation office

HF.name: Contract administration office
HF.desc: The office responsible for the administration of a contract.

HH.name: Audit office
HH.desc: The office responsible for conducting audits.

HJ.name: Foreign disclosure information office
HJ.desc: The office that reviews sensitive information for foreign disclosure.

HK.name: Mark-for party

The party within an organization for whom the material is marked to be

HL.name: Party to receive reports
HL.desc: The party to whom reports are to be submitted.

HM.name: Alternative manufacturer
HM.desc: Party identification of an alternative manufacturer for a product.

HN.name: Service performer
HN.desc: The party who is performing a service.

HP.name: Final message recipient

HQ.name: Account owner
HQ.desc: Identifies the owner of the account.

HR.name: Shipping line service
HR.desc: Identifies the shipping line service organization.

HS.name: Creditor
HS.desc: Party to whom payment is due.

HT.name: Clearing house

HU.name: Ordering bank

HV.name: Receiver of funds

HW.name: Sender of funds

HX.name: Debtor
HX.desc: Party from whom payment is due.

HY.name: Presenting bank

I1.name: Intermediary bank 1

A financial institution between the ordered bank and the beneficiary's

I2.name: Intermediary bank 2
I2.desc:
A financial institution between the ordered bank and the beneficiary's
                                    bank.

IB.name: Intermediary/broker
IB.desc:
A person intervening between parties to produce agreement or
                                    reconciliation.

ID.name: Replacing manufacturer
ID.desc:
A code used to identify a party who replaces the previous party for
                                    the manufacture of an article.

IE.name: Non-resident third party company with whom financial account is held
IE.desc:
Identifies the non-resident third party company with whom the
                                    financial account is held.

IF.name: Non-resident group company with whom financial account is held
IF.desc:
Identifies the non-resident group company with whom the financial
                                    account is held.

IG.name: Non-resident beneficiary
IG.desc:
The ultimate non-resident recipient of the funds. Normally the account
                                    owner who is reimbursed by the payor.

IH.name: Resident beneficiary
IH.desc:
The ultimate resident recipient of the funds. Normally the account
                                    owner who is reimbursed by the payor.

IJ.name: Non-resident instructing party
IJ.desc: Identifies the non-resident party originating the instruction.

IL.name: Resident instructing party
IL.desc: Identifies the resident party originating the instruction.

IM.name: Importer
IM.desc:
(3020) Party who makes - or on whose behalf a Customs clearing agent
                                    or other authorized person makes - an import declaration. This may include a person
                                    who has possession of the goods or to whom the goods are consigned.

IN.name: Insurer
IN.desc: A person or company offering insurance policies for premiums.

IO.name: Insurance company
IO.desc: A company engaged in the business of insurance.

IP.name: Insurance claim adjuster
IP.desc: A party which adjusts losses on behalf of an insurer.

IQ.name: Domestic financial institution
IQ.desc: Domestic party acting as financial institution.

IR.name: Non-domestic financial institution
IR.desc: Non-domestic party acting as financial institution.

IS.name: Party to receive certified inspection report
IS.desc: Party (at buyer) to receive certified inspection report.

IT.name: Installation on site
IT.desc: A party who possesses the site on which an installation shall be made.

IU.name: Non-resident debtor
IU.desc:
Non-resident party who makes the payment or against whom a claim
                                    exists.

IV.name: Invoicee
IV.desc: (3006) Party to whom an invoice is issued.

IW.name: Non-resident creditor
IW.desc:
Non-resident party receiving the payment or against whom a liability
                                    exists.

IX.name: Supplier work team
IX.desc: The supplier's team responsible for performing the work.

IY.name: Tenant manager
IY.desc:
A code to identify the party who rents the rights to use the goodwill
                                    and facilities of an enterprise.

IZ.name: Party mandated to liquidate an enterprise
IZ.desc:
A code to identify the party who has been legally mandated to sell off
                                    an enterprise.

JA.name: Certified accountant
JA.desc: Code identifying the party as a certified accountant.

JB.name: Goods collection party
JB.desc: Party that will collect or has collected the goods.

JC.name: Party at final place of positioning
JC.desc: Identifies the party at the final place of positioning.

JD.name: Customs office of clearance
JD.desc: Identifies the office where customs clearance procedures take place.

JE.name: Party from whom customs documents are to be picked up
JE.desc:
Identification of the party from whom customs documents are to be
                                    picked up.

JF.name: Party from whom non-customs documents are to be picked up
JF.desc:
Identification of the party from whom non-customs documents are to be
                                    picked up.

JG.name: Party to receive customs documents
JG.desc:
Identification of the party to whom customs documents are to be
                                    delivered.

JH.name: Party to receive non-customs documents
JH.desc:
Identification of the party to whom non-customs documents are to be
                                    delivered.

LA.name: Party designated to provide living animal care
LA.desc: Party responsible to take care of transported living animals.

LB.name: Co-producer
LB.desc: A code used to identify a party who participates in production.

LC.name: Party declaring the Value Added Tax (VAT)
LC.desc:
A code to identify the party who is responsible for declaring the
                                    Value Added Tax (VAT) on the sale of goods or services.

LD.name: Party recovering the Value Added Tax (VAT)
LD.desc:
A code to identify the party who is eligible to recover the Value
                                    Added Tax (VAT) on the sale of goods or services.

LE.name: Person on claim
LE.desc: To identify the person who is the subject of the claim.

LF.name: Buyer's corporate office
LF.desc: The identification of the buyer's corporate office.

LG.name: Supplier's corporate office
LG.desc: The identification of the supplier's corporate office.

LH.name: Liquidator
LH.desc: The party responsible for settling or paying a debt.

LI.name: Account coordinator
LI.desc:
An individual with coordination responsibilities for a specific
                                    account.

LJ.name: Inspection leader
LJ.desc: An individual responsible for an inspection team.

LK.name: Patient
LK.desc: A person receiving or registered to receive medical treatment.

LM.name: Medical treatment executant
LM.desc: The party who executes a medical treatment.

LO.name: Medical treatment prescriber
LO.desc: The party who prescribes a medical treatment.

LP.name: Loading party
LP.desc: Party responsible for the loading when other than carrier.

LQ.name: Debt payment authorisation party
LQ.desc: A party which authorises the payment of a debt.

LS.name: Product services and repairs centre
LS.desc: A centre which services and repairs products.

LU.name: Entry point technical assessment group
LU.desc: Party acts as an entry point for technical assessment.

LV.name: Party assigning a status
LV.desc: Party responsible for assigning a status.

MA.name: Party for whom item is ultimately intended
MA.desc: Party for whom item is ultimately intended.

MG.name: Party designated to execute re-icing
MG.desc:
Party designated to execute re-icing, selected in the official list of
                                    mandatories competent for this kind of operation.

MI.name: Planning schedule/material release issuer
MI.desc: A party issuing a planning schedule/material release.

MP.name: Manufacturing unit
MP.desc: A party acting as a particular production unit of a manufacturer.

MR.name: Message recipient
MR.desc: A party to receive a message or messages.

MS.name: Document/message issuer/sender
MS.desc: Issuer of a document and/or sender of a message.

MT.name: Party designated to execute sanitary procedures
MT.desc: A party which is designated to execute sanitary procedures.

N1.name: Notify party no. 1
N1.desc: The first party which is to be notified.

N2.name: Notify party no. 2
N2.desc: The second party which is to be notified.

NI.name: Notify party
NI.desc: (3180) Party to be notified of arrival of goods.

OA.name: Break bulk berth operator
OA.desc:
Party who offers facilities for berthing of vessels, handling and
                                    storage of break bulk cargo.

OC.name: Party data responsible party
OC.desc: The party responsible for all party data.

OD.name: Equipment repair party
OD.desc: A party making repairs to equipment.

OF.name: On behalf of
OF.desc: Party on behalf of which an action is executed.

OG.name: Owner or lessor's surveyor
OG.desc: Surveyor hired by the owner or lessor of the item.

OH.name: Lessee's surveyor
OH.desc: Surveyor hired by the lessee of the item.

OI.name: Outside inspection agency
OI.desc: Third party inspecting goods or equipment.

OJ.name: Third party
OJ.desc: Another party besides the two principals.

OK.name: Receiver's sub-entity
OK.desc: Identifies a sub-entity within the receiver's organization.

OL.name: Case of need party
OL.desc: Party to be approached in case of difficulty.

OM.name: Collecting bank
OM.desc:
Any bank, other than the remitting bank, involved in processing the
                                    collection.

ON.name: Remitting bank
ON.desc:
The bank to which the principal has entrusted the handling of a
                                    collection.

OO.name: Order of the shipper party
OO.desc:
The owner of goods under consignment which are moving under a
                                    negotiable transport document and will only be released upon receipt of the original
                                    transport document.

OP.name: Operator of property or equipment
OP.desc: The party which operates property or a unit of equipment.

OQ.name: Collection principal
OQ.desc: The party entrusting the handling of a collection to a bank.

OR.name: Ordered bank
OR.desc: Identifies the account servicer for the ordering customer or payor.

OS.name: Original shipper
OS.desc: The original supplier of the goods.

OT.name: Outside test agency
OT.desc: Third party testing goods, equipment or services.

OU.name: Account owner's servicing bank on the sending side
OU.desc:
Identifies the financial institution on the sending side which
                                    services the account owner's bank account(s).

OV.name: Owner of means of transport
OV.desc:
(3126) Party owning the means of transport. No synonym of carrier =
                                    CA.

OW.name: Account owner's servicing bank on the receiving side
OW.desc:
Identifies the financial institution on the receiving side which
                                    services the account owner's bank account(s).

OX.name: Sender's correspondent bank
OX.desc:
The account, or branch of the sender, or another financial
                                    institution, through which the sender will reimburse the receiver.

OY.name: Ordering customer
OY.desc: Identifies the originator of the instruction.

OZ.name: Receiver's correspondent bank
OZ.desc:
The branch of the receiver, or another financial institution, at which
                                    the funds will be made available to the receiver.

PA.name: Party to receive inspection report
PA.desc: Party to whom the inspection report should be sent.

PB.name: Paying financial institution
PB.desc: Financial institution designated to make payment.

PC.name: Actual purchaser's customer
PC.desc:
Party the purchaser within the actual message is selling the ordered
                                    goods or services to.

PE.name: Payee
PE.desc: Identifies the credit party when other than the beneficiary.

PF.name: Party to receive freight bill
PF.desc: Party to whom the freight bill should be sent.

PG.name: Prime contractor
PG.desc: Party responsible for the whole project if other than the buyer.

PH.name: Payer's financial institution
PH.desc:
Institution chosen by the payer to execute financial transactions on
                                    his behalf.

PJ.name: Party to receive correspondence
PJ.desc:
Second party designated by a first party to receive certain
                                    correspondence in lieu of it being mailed directly to this first party.

PL.name: Payor
PL.desc:
Identifies the debit party when other than the ordering customer (for
                                    banking purposes).

PM.name: Party to receive paper memo of invoice
PM.desc: Party being informed about invoice issue (via paper).

PN.name: Party to receive shipping notice
PN.desc: The party is to be the recipient of the shipping notice.

PO.name: Ordering party
PO.desc: To be used only if ordering party and buyer are not identical.

PS.name: Payer's company name/ID (Check, Draft or Wire)
PS.desc: Party to send cheque, draft or wire for payment.

PT.name: Party to receive test report
PT.desc: A party which is named to be the recipient of test reports.

PW.name: Despatch party
PW.desc:
(3282) Party where goods are collected or taken over by the carrier
                                    (i.e. if other than consignor).

PX.name: Party to receive all documents
PX.desc: A party which is named to be the recipient of all documents.

PY.name: Checking party
PY.desc:
Party or contact designated on behalf of carrier or his agent to
                                    establish the actual figures for quantities, weight, volume and/or (cube)
                                    measurements of goods or containers which are to appear in the transport contract
                                    and on which charges will be based.

PZ.name: Party to print some document
PZ.desc: The party that is to print a specific document.

RA.name: Central bank or regulatory authority
RA.desc:
Identifies central bank or regulatory authority which must be informed
                                    of certain aspects of a message.

RB.name: Receiving financial institution
RB.desc: Financial institution designated to receive payment.

RE.name: Party to receive commercial invoice remittance
RE.desc:
Party to whom payment for a commercial invoice or bill should be
                                    remitted.

RF.name: Received from
RF.desc: Name of a person or department which actually delivers the goods.

RH.name: Seller's financial institution
RH.desc:
Financial institution designated by seller to receive payment. RDFI
                                    (ACH transfers).

RI.name: Reinsurance intermediary/broker
RI.desc: Intermediary party between ceding company and reinsurance.

RL.name: Reporting carrier (Customs)
RL.desc: Party who makes the cargo report to Customs.

RM.name: Reporting carrier's nominated agent/representative (Customs)
RM.desc:
Agent who formally makes a cargo report to Customs on behalf of the
                                    carrier.

RP.name: Routing party
RP.desc: Party responsible for the selection of the carrier(s).

RS.name: Party to receive statement of account
RS.desc: Party to whom the statement of account should be sent.

RV.name: Receiver of cheque
RV.desc:
Identifies the party which is to receive the actual cheque, when
                                    different from the receiver of funds.

RW.name: Issuer of waybill
RW.desc: Party issuing the contract (waybill) for carriage.

SB.name: Sales responsibility
SB.desc: A party being responsible for sales.

SE.name: Seller
SE.desc: (3346) Party selling merchandise to a buyer.

SF.name: Ship from
SF.desc:
Identification of the party from where goods will be or have been
                                    shipped.

SG.name: Store group
SG.desc: A chain of shops or stores.

SI.name: Shipping schedule issuer
SI.desc: The party which issues a shipping schedule.

SN.name: Store keeper
SN.desc: A party keeping a shop or store.

SO.name: Sold to if different than bill to
SO.desc:
Party to whom the goods have been sold, if different to the bill to
                                    party.

SR.name: Seller's agent/representative
SR.desc:
(3254) Party representing the seller for the purpose of the trade
                                    transaction.

ST.name: Ship to
ST.desc:
Identification of the party to where goods will be or have been
                                    shipped.

SU.name: Supplier
SU.desc: Party who supplies goods and/or services.

SX.name: Surety for additions
SX.desc:
Natural of legal person (generally a bank of insurance company) who
                                    accepts responsibility in due legal form for the financial guarantee to Customs of
                                    the payment of additional duties or fees that become due against a particular
                                    shipment, which have not previously been covered by surety.

SY.name: Surety
SY.desc:
Natural or legal person (generally a bank or insurance company) who
                                    accepts responsibility in due legal form for the financial consequences of
                                    non-fulfillment of another's obligations to the Customs (CCC).

SZ.name: Surety for antidumping/countervailing duty
SZ.desc:
Natural or legal person that has been contracted by the importer to
                                    guarantee to Customs the payment of antidumping and/or countervailing duties that
                                    become due against a particular shipment.

TA.name: Legal receiver
TA.desc: The party responsible for a receivership.

TB.name: Submitter
TB.desc: To specify that the party is a submitter.

TCP.name: Transit charge payer
TCP.desc:
Party, other than the ordering party, which has to pay the charges
                                    concerning the transit operations.

TD.name: Party to receive technical documentation
TD.desc: Party to whom technical documentation should be sent.

TE.name: Bankruptcy referee
TE.desc: To specify that the party is a referee in a bankruptcy case.

TF.name: Source of information
TF.desc: To specify that the party is the source of information.

TG.name: Judge
TG.desc: To specify that the party is a judge.

TH.name: Attorney
TH.desc: To specify that the party is an attorney.

TI.name: Law firm
TI.desc: To specify that the party is a law firm.

TJ.name: Trustee
TJ.desc: To specify that the party is a trustee.

TK.name: Signatory
TK.desc: To specify that the party is a signatory.

TN.name: Subject of inquiry
TN.desc: The party is the subject of an inquiry.

TP.name: Owner of residence
TP.desc: Identifies the owner of a residence.

TR.name: Terminal operator
TR.desc: A party which handles the loading and unloading of marine vessels.

TS.name: Party to receive certified test results
TS.desc: Party to whom the certified test results should be sent.

TT.name: Transfer to
TT.desc: The party which is the recipient of a transfer.

TZ.name: Military branch
TZ.desc: Identifies the branch of the military.

UA.name: Educational institution
UA.desc: Identifies a university, college or school.

UC.name: Ultimate consignee
UC.desc:
Party who has been designated on the invoice or packing list as the
                                    final recipient of the stated merchandise.

UG.name: Merged company with retained identity
UG.desc: Company whose identity has been retained from a merger.

UHP.name: Unexpected handling party
UHP.desc:
Party authorized (during a voyage) to apply unexpected handling
                                    procedures or party having applied these procedures.

UM.name: Party not to be confused with
UM.desc: Identifies a party not to be confused with another party.

UP.name: Unloading party
UP.desc: A party to unload the goods.

UT.name: Merged company
UT.desc: Identifies the company involved in a merger.

VL.name: Party manufactured for
VL.desc: Identifies the party for whom manufacturing of goods is done.

VP.name: Receiver manager
VP.desc:
Manager of a business which is in receivership status and which will
                                    not be liquidated.

VV.name: Ultimate same country parent company
VV.desc: Identifies the highest level parent company in the same country.

VW.name: Responsible party
VW.desc: Identifies the party that can be called to account.

VX.name: Secured party
VX.desc: Identifies a party that is guaranteed against loss.

VY.name: Other related party
VY.desc: Identifies an entity as an unspecified but related party.

VZ.name: Co-debtor
VZ.desc: Identifies an entity as a joint or mutual debtor.

WA.name: Company which holds financial interest
WA.desc:
Identifies a company which holds any financial stake in an undertaking
                                    or organization.

WB.name: Rating organization
WB.desc:
Identifies an organization responsible for assigning a classification
                                    or rating.

WC.name: Information reference agency
WC.desc: The agency responsible for the reference of information.

WD.name: Warehouse depositor
WD.desc: (3004) Party depositing goods in a warehouse.

WE.name: Compilation agency
WE.desc: The agency responsible for the compilation of information.

WF.name: Information maintenance agency
WF.desc: The agency responsible for the maintenance of information.

WG.name: Information dissemination agency
WG.desc: The agency responsible for the dissemination of information.

WH.name: Warehouse keeper
WH.desc: (3022) Party taking responsibility for goods entered into a warehouse.

WI.name: Inspection address
WI.desc: Specifies the address for an inspection.

WJ.name: Refusal party
WJ.desc: Identification of the party responsible for a refusal.

WK.name: Value added network provider
WK.desc:
A party that provides telecommunications interconnectivity services in
                                    an electronic data interchange environment.

WL.name: Agency
WL.desc: The business or establishment of an agent.

WN.name: Party to receive order to supply
WN.desc:
Party designated by the registering party to receive a binding
                                    direction to supply something.

WO.name: Party to receive invitation to offer
WO.desc: An entity to receive an invitation to offer.

WP.name: Sub-entity
WP.desc: A part into which an entity has been divided.

WPA.name: Weighting party
WPA.desc: Party designated (legally accepted) to ascertain the weight.

WQ.name: Doing business as
WQ.desc: The name under which business is conducted.

WR.name: Party submitting quote
WR.desc: The party stating the price of something to be purchased.

WS.name: Wholesaler
WS.desc:
Seller of articles, often in large quantities, to be retailed by
                                    others.

WT.name: Affiliated party
WT.desc: A party attached or connected to another party.

WU.name: Previous name
WU.desc: Name of an entity used before the current name.

WV.name: Party performing task
WV.desc: An entity responsible for performing a task to be undertaken.

ZZZ.name: Mutually defined
ZZZ.desc: Party specification mutually agreed between interchanging parties.
